## Three deployment surfaces — ask before building

| Surface | Org type | Data | What to build |
|---------|----------|------|---------------|
| **Local prototype** | None — Vite only | JS fixtures in `src/modules/data/` | LBC/SLDS UI only, no wiring |
| **Front-end org** | Evergreen, sandbox, scratch without cloud perms | None — UI shell only | LBC/SLDS UI only, no wiring |
| **Enabled org** | Sandbox or production with cloud/object permissions | Live Salesforce data | LBC/SLDS UI + data wiring |

Always ask: **Is this front-end only, or does it connect to real org data?**

- Front-end only → no `@wire`, no Apex, use empty/hardcoded states
- Enabled org with data → invoke `prd-to-salesforce-ui` skill before choosing a wire adapter or writing Apex

## Where to put new code

| What | Where |
|------|-------|
| Deployable component | `force-app/main/default/lwc/<name>/` |
| Route-level local view | `src/modules/page/<name>/` + route in `src/routes.config.js` + import in `shell/app/app.js` |
| Reusable local UI | `src/modules/ui/<name>/` |

